SUMMARY:Build a Pizza Ordering Agent with Microsoft Foundry and MCP
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nIn this hands-on session\, you will
  learn how to create intelligent\, domain-specific AI agents using the Mic
 rosoft Foundry Agent Service.\n\nWe will walk through the process step by 
 step — from building a basic agent to extending it with custom tools\, e
 xternal data\, and live integrations.\n\nBy the end of the workshop\, you 
 will have built your own Contoso PizzaBot\, an AI assistant capable of:\n\
 n* Following customized system prompts\n* Using retrieval-augmented genera
 tion (RAG) to answer questions based on custom documents\n* Calling custom
  tools\, such as a pizza calculator\n* Integrating with an MCP server for 
 real-time menu and order management\n\nPre-requisites:\n\n* A browser and 
 access to the [Azure Portal](https://aka.ms/PortalAzure)\n* An Azure subsc
 ription provided or use your own: https://aka.ms/GetAzureSubscription\n* A
  [development environment](https://aka.ms/Python3.10/Config) with Python 3
 .13+ installed\n* Familiarity with Python basics (no deep AI background re
 quired!)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3134
 48337/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260220T173004Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260220T173004Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
